			<div class="content" id="post-content-2246327">
									

<blockquote>
<p>&#8230;why go &quot;THIS DOCUMENT IS DAMAGED&quot; when the documents from the non-German facility would have been moved back to Germany and thus would have been damaged as well?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Uh&#8230; What? The Nazis opened Pandora's box here, man. They lost their home the same way the British lost theirs.</p>
<p>As far as the other complaints and commentaries are concerned: yes, this is pretty damn cliché, and yes, the other major participants in the Second World War did some pretty crazy shit. This was inspired by frustration at a lack of an Abrahamic Behemoth on the site when we already have a couple Leviathans, and the (very stupid) theoretical Landkreuzer P.1500 Monster self-propelled artillery piece. I originally wanted to skipify the idea (and I might later) but the Reimagining Contest came up, and I took advantage of it. I have no delusions that this will win the contest, and mostly wanted to get my toes in the water with WWII Foundation fiction.</p>
<p>If I can come up with a way to improve this after the contest, I will, and I appreciate your input, regardless of your final assessment.</p>

